column1: †Up-To-Date:  Four doses of polio vaccine (three doses are acceptable if at least one dose was received on or after the fourth birthday); and
five DTP/DT vaccine doses (four doses are acceptable if at least one dose was received on or after the fourth birthday); and two doses of
measles-containing vaccine, at least one of which must be measles, mumps, and rubella combined.   Both doses must have been received on
or after the first birthday; and three doses of hepatitis B vaccine; and one dose of varicella vaccine or
physician-documented varicella (chickenpox) disease.
*Conditional Entrant is a student who does not currently meet all requirements.  This student must be followed up because he/she lacks but is not yet due for a required dose;
has a physician affidavit of Temporary Medical Exemption for one or more doses; or is a transfer student who has no record available yet.
**A Permanent Medical Exemption (PME): granted upon the filing with the school of a written statement from a licensed physician to the effect
that the physical condition of the student or medical circumstances relating to the student are such that immunization is permanently not indicated.
§ A Personal Belief Exemption (PBE), whereby a parent requests exemption from the immunization requirements for school entry because all or some immunizations are contrary to the parent's beliefs.

§§  A Health Care Practitioner (HCP) Counseled Personal Belief Exemption (PBE) obtained by the parent who provides documentation that a health care practitioner has informed the parent  regarding 1) the benefits and risks of immunization,
2) the health risks to the student and to the community of the communicable diseases for which immunization is required in CA

§§§  A Religious Exemption whereby a parent signs an affidavit requesting an exemption from the immunization because s/he is a member of a religion which prohibits him/her from seeking medical advice or treatment from
authorized health care practitioners
§§§§  Subject to exclusion from school
†† 4 or more doses of any diphtheria and tetanus toxoids and   pertussis vaccines including diphtheria and tetanus toxoids,
and any acellular pertussis vaccine (DTaP/DTP/DT).
¥ 3 or more doses of polio vaccine;  Oral polio vaccine (OPV) or inactivated polio vaccine (IPV) or any combination of these.
‡ 2 doses of measles-mumps-rubella vaccine.
§ 3 or more doses of Hepatitis B vaccine.
¶ 1 or more doses of varicella at or after child's first birthday, unadjusted for history of varicella illness.
¶¶   Fall reports were due October 15, 2015 and reporting closed on December 4, 2015
^ Vaccine-specific compliance rates presented here should be considered minimum rates, since PBE and PME vaccine histories are not reported and some PBE/PME may be vaccinated and compliant.
